- VSCode Version: 1.10.2 [commit 8076a19]
- OS Version: Windows 10
![image](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/2474675/23722601/d5b2d43e-03fa-11e7-95b3-621b82ca8a58.png)


##  Steps to Reproduce:

1. Create a sample C# app with multiple code blocks on the same line:
![image](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/2474675/23721519/ea63d670-03f6-11e7-9c57-a7422d80fd14.png)

2. Set multiple column breakpoints on the line **while not debugging**
![image](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/2474675/23721553/10ba467e-03f7-11e7-9f48-504dd15df34f.png)

3. F5 the app

## Results:
**Expected:** setBreakpoints request has multiple breakpoints on the same line

**Actual:** setBreakpoints request only has the first breakpoint from that line, causing the remaining ones to disappear once the debugger sends a response
![image](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/2474675/23721736/b0a553d6-03f7-11e7-9ce9-d737a580d7a1.png)


